===Definitions===
{{head|zh|hanzi}}

# to become [[drunk]]; to become [[intoxicated]]
#: {{zh-x|喝醉|to become drunk}}
#* {{zh-x|厭 厭 夜 飲，不 醉 無 歸。|Happily and long into the night we drink; till all '''are drunk''', there is no retiring.|ref=Shijing}}
#* {{zh-x|漁父 見 而 問 之 曰：「子 非 三閭大夫 與{yú}？何故 至 於 斯！」<br>^屈 ^原 曰：「舉世 皆 濁 我 獨 清，眾人 皆 醉 我 獨 醒，是以 見 放！」|The fisherman saw him and asked: "Were you not the ''sanlü dafu'' [a high position in the Chu court]? How have you ended up like this?"<br>{{w|Qu Yuan}} said: "The whole world was muddy and I was clean alone; all men '''were drunk''' and I was sober alone; and I was exiled for that!"|ref=Chuci}}
# to [[intoxicate]]; to make someone [[drunk]]
#* {{zh-x|許 之，飲 先 從 者 酒，醉 之，竊 馬 而 獻 之 ^子-常，^子-常 歸 ^唐 侯。|When they were allowed this, they made the earlier attendants drink alcohol, '''making''' them '''drunk'''; stole their horses; and presented them to Zichang. Zichang then let the marquis return to Tang.|ref=Zuozhuan}}
#* {{zh-x|酒 不 醉 人 人 自 醉，色 不 迷 人 人 自 迷。|Alcohol does not '''intoxicate''' men, men are intoxicated by themselves; women do not infatuate men, men are infatuated by themselves.|ref=Jinpingmei}}
# to be [[fascinated]] with; to be [[enchanted]] by; to be [[crazy]] about; to be [[addicted]] to
#: {{zh-x|醉心|to be infatuated with}}
# to [[marinate]] in [[cooking]] [[wine]]
#: {{zh-x|醉蝦|'''drunken''' shrimp {{q|dish name}}}}
# {{lb|zh|literary}} to [[drink]] [[alcoholic]] [[drink]] [[moderately]]

